Package: ShinyPsych
Type: Package
Title: An easy way to program psychology experiments using Shiny
Version: 0.2.4
Authors@R: c(person("Markus", "Steiner", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "markus.d.steiner@gmail.com"),
             person("Nathaniel", "Phillips", role = "aut", email = "Nathaniel.D.Phillips.is@gmail.com"),
             person("Kevin", "Trutmann", role = "aut", email = "k.trutmann@gmail.com"))
Author: Markus D. Steiner [aut, cre],
        Nathaniel D. Phillips [aut],
        Kevin Trutmann [aut]
Maintainer: Markus Steiner <markus.d.steiner@gmail.com>
Description: ShinyPsych is a package developed to simplify programming experiments in that can be run locally or online. It provides functions to create display and save data from questionnaires and a collection of experimental tasks often used in psychological research (currently n armed bandit task, balloon analogue risk task (BART), decisions from description (DfD), decisions from experience (DfE) and delay discounting (DD)).
